definition.value: A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 24 carbons and 1 double bond.
A member of the class of  benzamides resulting from the formal condensation of 4-amino-5-chloro-2-methoxybenzoic acid with the primary amino group of N,N-diethylethane-1,2-diamine.
A sphingomyelin d18:1 in which the fatty acyl group contains 26 carbons and is fully saturated.
